{"id":31818,"date":"2019-06-08T16:16:40","date_gmt":"2019-06-08T12:16:40","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=31818"},"modified":"2025-04-23T10:00:14","modified_gmt":"2025-04-23T06:00:14","slug":"five-divine-punishments-sins","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/06\/08\/five-divine-punishments-sins\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Consequences: Five collevtive punishments for deadly sins"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Ibn Abbas reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201c<strong>Five sins come with five afflictions: People do not violate their covenant except that their enemies are given power over them. They do not judge with anything other than Allah&#8217;s revelation except that poverty will be spread among them. Obscenity does not prevail among them except that death will be spread among them. They do not cheat in measurements except that crops are prevented from growing, so they suffer years of drought. They do not withhold the obligatory charity except that the sky will hold back its rain.<\/strong>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: al-Mu\u2019jam al-Kabi\u0304r lil-T\u0323abara\u0304ni\u0304 10992<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <i>Hasan <\/i>(fair) according to Al-Albani<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0651\u064e\u0627\u0633\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e \u062e\u064e\u0645\u0652\u0633\u064c \u0628\u0650\u062e\u064e\u0645\u0652\u0633\u064d \u0645\u064e\u0627 \u0646\u064e\u0642\u064e\u0636\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0648\u0652\u0645\u064c \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0639\u064e\u0647\u0652\u